    {
      "tenantId": "dryrun/kody-chat",
      "taskKey": "2",
      "kind": "followups",
      "doc": [
        {
          "title": "Reconcile existing finding once a healthy observation lands",
          "body": "findings/finding-repo-ci-main.json currently sits open with severity=high even though CI has been green for prior main runs. After PR #3 merges and a scheduled observer run records one healthy observation against an in_progress finding, confirm the reconciliation flow advances the finding (or hands it to verification). The agency-observer test 'creates one finding, updates it, and hands recovery to verification' covers the logic but has not been exercised against the live main branch yet.",
          "rationale": "The reconciliation flow depends on prior observation IDs being present. The first healthy observation after this fix should naturally advance the open finding through to in_progress/closed; if it doesn't, there is a separate bug somewhere else (reconcileFinding or the live finding file).",
          "priority": "medium"
        },
        {
          "title": "Verify the relay FD-collision fix in production",
          "body": "The terminal-bridge PTY relay fix in packages/fly/src/plugin/terminal/bridge.ts is exercised only by the test harness path. In production, an external launcher passes FD 3 as a real control channel, so the new guard (control_fd = None when it would alias master) is a no-op there. Confirm during the next terminal-bridge session that resize messages still flow through the control channel — the runtime test 'forwards browser resize messages to the PTY relay' covers it locally but a live smoke is worth doing once.",
          "rationale": "Production launcher wiring is not covered by unit tests. The guard is defensive — it skips the control channel only when it would alias master, which never happens in production — but the integration still needs confirmation.",
          "priority": "low"
        }
      ],
      "updatedAt": "2026-07-15T14:04:54.517Z"
    },
